Wash and dry all produce. Thinly slice @Romaine Lettuce{1%unit}(thinly sliced) and @Scallions{2%unit}(thinly sliced). Halve and peel @Yellow Onion{1%unit}(halved and peeled). Dice one half; thinly slice the other. Core and seed @Poblano Pepper{2%unit}(cored, seeded, and thinly sliced), then thinly slice. Roughly chop @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}(roughly chopped). Chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}(chopped). Halve @Lime{1%unit}(halved).

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add diced onion and cook until softened, about ~{3%minutes}. Add @Ground Beef{16%ounce}, breaking it up into pieces. Cook until browned and no longer pink, ~{6-7%minutes}. Toss in @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon} and @Mexican Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Add poblanos and sliced onion to same pan over medium-high heat. Cook, tossing, until softened, ~{6-7%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

> TIP: If you're having trouble getting the veggies to soften, add a splash of water.

Meanwhile, toss tomatoes, scallions, a squeeze of lime, and cilantro in a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper. In a #large bowl{}, toss half the romaine, a squeeze of lime, and a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Put @Refried Beans{1%box} in a #small bowl{} and microwave on high until warmed through, about ~{1%minute}. Wrap @Flour Tortilla{4%unit} in a damp #paper towel{} and microwave on high until warm, about ~{30%seconds}.

> TIP: Alternatively, heat beans in a small pan over medium-low heat; wrap tortillas in foil and warm in oven for 5 minutes at 400 degrees.

When everything is ready, set up a station for the burritos. Place refried beans, beef, veggies, tomato salsa, remaining romaine, sour cream, and @Cheddar Cheese{1%cup} in individual plates or bowls and invite everyone to wrap their own burritos. Serve with salad on the side.